ing church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705205,"age":69,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705206,"age":71,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Sarah Berks was born in 1500, in Nottinghamshire, England, her father, Ralph Berks, was 20 and her mother, Elizabeth Gresswell, was 20. She had at least 1 son with Marmaduke William Neepe. She died in 1580, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 80."},"et":{"1500–1580":"1500–1580","1525–1600":"1525–1600","1480–1560":"1480–1560","1525":"1525","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1600":"1600","1500":"1500","1560":"1560","1571":"1571","1580":"1580","1480":"1480","1549":"1549","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England","Southwell, Nottinghamshire, England":"Southwell, Nottinghamshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1500–1580":"1500–1580","1525–1600":"1525–1600","1480–1560":"1480–1560","1525":"1525","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1600":"1600","1500":"1500","1560":"1560","1571":"1571","1580":"1580","1480":"1480","1549":"1549","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England","Southwell, Nottinghamshire, England":"Southwell, Nottinghamshire, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1500–1580":"1500–1580","1525–1600":"1525–1600","1480–1560":"1480–1560","1525":"1525","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1600":"1600","1500":"1500","1560":"1560","1571":"1571","1580":"1580","1480":"1480","1549":"1549","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Angleterre","Southwell, Nottinghamshire, England":"Southwell, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre","